      <section eId="sec_CHC-1302-4">
        <num>CHC 1302.4</num>
        <heading>1302.4.  Simultaneous proceedings</heading>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1302-4__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>A tribunal of this state may exercise jurisdiction to establish a support order if the
petition or comparable pleading is filed after a pleading is filed in another state or a foreign
country only if:</p>
          </content>
          <paragraph eId="CHC-1302-4__subsec_A__subsec_1">
            <num>(1)</num>
            <content>
              <p>The petition or comparable pleading in this state is filed before the expiration of
the time allowed in the other state or the foreign country for filing a responsive pleading
challenging the exercise of jurisdiction by the other state or the foreign country;</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CHC-1302-4__subsec_A__subsec_2">
            <num>(2)</num>
            <content>
              <p>The contesting party timely challenges the exercise of jurisdiction in the other
state or the foreign country; and</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CHC-1302-4__subsec_A__subsec_3">
            <num>(3)</num>
            <content>
              <p>If relevant, this state is the home state of the child.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1302-4__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>A tribunal of this state may not exercise jurisdiction to establish a support order
if the petition or comparable pleading is filed before a petition or comparable pleading is
filed in another state or a foreign country if:</p>
          </content>
          <paragraph eId="CHC-1302-4__subsec_B__subsec_1">
            <num>(1)</num>
            <content>
              <p>The petition or comparable pleading in the other state or foreign country is filed
before the expiration of the time allowed in this state for filing a responsive pleading
challenging the exercise of jurisdiction by this state;</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CHC-1302-4__subsec_B__subsec_2">
            <num>(2)</num>
            <content>
              <p>The contesting party timely challenges the exercise of jurisdiction in this state;
and</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CHC-1302-4__subsec_B__subsec_3">
            <num>(3)</num>
            <content>
              <p>If relevant, the other state or foreign country is the home state of the child.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
        </subsection>
